reviews:
I stayed two nights in the hotel. The room was small, i walked around in white socks and they were black afterwards. Breakfast was very small, no Muesli and no fresh fruits. I will book another hotel next time.
On the positive side: The staff was extremly nice, and the shower gel and shampoo was good by L'occitane.

I stayed in a family room for 3 nights with my 2 daughters on a bed and breakfast basis. The room was small and cozy but really only used to sleep in as we were out all day. The beds were very comfortable and room cleaned daily with fresh towels. We we’re situation on the second floor but had no noice disturbance at all from any of the other rooms. The bathroom was a little worn but clean, water pressure in the shower was quite impressive which is always a bonus. I would definitely stay at this hotel again due to its location but without the breakfast option. We found the choice at breakfast very limited. Only on one occasion was there someone around in the dining area, so if things had run out like the fresh coffee there was no one to ask if it could be refilled. There was a choice of hot and cold breakfast but as mentioned very limited choice.

The hotel was easy to access, close to the metro. Great location, just round the corner from the Arc de Triomph. Friendly staff who were happy to help. Breakfast had good choice. Rooms were clean and good size. We had a triple room. Very happy

Hotel Arc de Triomphe is right in the center of Paris, extremely close to the Champs Elysées and walking distance from the Metro. The staff were incredible and so friendly with wonderful suggestions on sightseeing and places to eat. They obliged my broken French and happily spoke with me and allowed me to practice! Also, breakfast was delicious and they had many options for juices and food in the morning as well as espresso. Very affordable and completely worth every penny! Room was incredibly comfortable and clean. Thank you for a wonderful stay, I will definitely be coming back!

This hotel is small, great part of the city and good on a budget. It does not have a lot of atmosphere but the place is clean and well run, friendly desk staff. Have only two rooms on each floor is great for family members traveling together.

Everything was perfect, the rooms, the service, the only thing is that when we arrived one day, A/C technicians were in the room without asking previously and we needed to wait.

Everything was excellent.

Very nice hotel with nice room.. We enjoyed our stay there a lot! The location is very very good. We had everything we needed in the room. It was clean an cosy. Thank you for making our trip this good

Good staying, the staff was friendly and helpful. Hotel is in a great location, about couple of minutes of walk to Arc de Triomphe. Breakfast buffet was 15€ for a day, kid was free. Hotel was quiet and beds very comfortable.

Very nice location just 4 minutes walk from the metro station near the Arc de Triomphe. The staff in the hotel are welcoming and very friendly specially Mr Yousri. The room was clean and quiet and had all the necessary favilities.

A kindly welcome, we had some problems, but the staff was promptly quick to fix it. the rooms are very small for a triple solution, also we had a good buffet for breakfast. Also a very quiet area near the Arc The Triomphe

Really nice hotel in a great location, about 5 minutes walk for the arc de Triomphe. Kind staff, comfortable and clean rooms. Maybe breakfast could be included in price. The people in reception kindly helped us in whatever we wanted

The hotel is 3 minutes away from the Arc de Triomphe, close to a very nice boulangerie, in a safe neighborhood. Staff ok, room cleaning every day.
Unfortunately it was a little bit cold, but not very. I will definitly recomand it!

Arrived with our 4 year old son on a Friday evening.The room(triple) was less spacious than we anticipated.The problem was that both the air conditioner and the radiator were not working so we ended up spending the night in a cold room.When I informed the lady at the reception the next morning about the problem,she informed me that we should wait for her colleague working the night shift and she could not do something in the meantime.Moreover,she sarcastically added that we should avoid opening the windows so as the room not to feel so cold.I immediately protested that this was unacceptable,especially when having a small child and either she should find another solution or give us another room.To this she replied with more yelling and irony.In the afternoon,after further protesting,she reluctantly provided a small plug-in electric radiator (even calling my wife names in the process for protesting)which by no means was suitable for adequately heating the room while it was freezing outside.As it is understandable,the reception’s unprovoked behaviour and heating problems ruined our experience.It is a pity because the location of the hotel is good.I hope they learn to treat paying customers better.

Clean hotel on good location, 2 rooms per level, top level 6 reachable by stairs.
Good breakfast in the basement of the hotel, versatile and fresh, and innovative on the space. Parking in nearby expensive public garage , expensive, or in the street if possible.

Spent 2 night at Hotel Arc de Triomphe and we had an excellent experience. Friendly staff, clean and well equipped rooms, spacious and overall amazing hotel. Thank you for making our stay in Paris comfortable.

Excellent little hotel, knowledgable front desk, great location near Ofccourse arc de triomf. Great restaurants nearby. Really liked this hotel, am often in Paris but may be the largest room 8n Paris inzage ever had (room7) Nice brand shampoo etc

Really nice hotel in a great location, staff very friendly. Breakfast was good to start the day. Metro was 2 minutes away and lots of restaurants nearby. Arc de triomphe is also a 2 minute walk from hotel. Hotel was quiet and beds very comfortable. Only 7 rooms in hotel so breakfast was never busy.

We were for two days on a short trip to Paris. We like the hotel service and location are great. From there you can walk for two minutes to be in the great area. Shopping restaurants and super markets .... thank you

We have just got home from a 2 night stay at this hotel and everything was just what we needed and perfect price to pay! I see people moaning about the size of the room/lift but why are you going to Paris to stay in your hotel room? We were never in our room so it served it’s purpose fantastically for us! The location was perfect literally a 2 minute walk to the Arc De Triomphe! I would 100% stay here again. The hotel staff were very helpful and friendly.

354 / 5.000
Rezultatele traducerii
star_border
Those who aim for a city break, have one location, located in the central area of Pasris, very close to all the important objectives and a very short distance from the Arc de Triomphe.
A few meters away is a Carrefour grocery store, as well as restaurant or terrace locations.
With a taxi order, you can reach any important location with 10-15 euros.

I haven't stayed at any other hotels in Paris, but I have stayed at hundreds of other hotels in general. This place was very welcoming, staff at the desk was always happy and willing to help. The location was perfect, we never got lost because we always just found our way to the Arc de triumph - when we return to Paris we will stay here again. Good service, good location, good price.

Hotel is very small and so was the room which we had. We were 3 adults and had a double bed and a sofa bed. The room was very basic and small. All the facilities need to be updated. Bathroom had basic sink and shower. The best thing I can say about the hotel is it’s convenience to Arc de Triomphe, which is 5 minutes walk. Don’t get confused ( as we did), there’s another hotel called Arc de Triomphe Etoile, so make sure you get the correct hotel. There is a lift, which is tiny and will take a person and a suitcase at a push.
Breakfast was in the basement and was okay.

The hotel is small but very nice. Excellent position really close to a metro station. Staff very kind and friendly. The room in which we stayed was comfortable and clean. Suggested for families. Breakfast buffet is good although not very various.

Great location in a quiet street near Arc de Triomphe and all the advantages of that.l Good breakfast and friendly helpful staff . Also good transport links to CDG airport Eiffel Tower Montmarte and anything else of interest.

Near metro station, very very close to the most vibrant place in the city, very nice and friendly staff.. Very clean.. Nice breakfast.. Vey good wifi.. I really enjoyed it.. It became my favourite hotel in the city

This was my second stay at the hotel. It was a wonderful stay. I was upgraded to a superior room without asking. The room was big compared to Paris room sizes. Loccitane toiletries. Special thanks for Yousri for making my stay memorable.

Perfect location - very close to Arc de Triomphe and a subway station. A lot of restaurants and cafes nearby. Comfortable bed, quiet room, daily cleaning service, staff had good English. A small lift.

The rooms are great (small but modern) and the staff are very helpful (special mention to Mr. Alex). it's located near the arc de triomphe, Champs Elysées and a collection of top restaurants and cafes. For its price its a real bargain.

Stayed for 3 day @ Hotel Arc de Triomphe waithing to start my Viking Cruise. Wonderful Hotel. Close within walking distance to sites & Shopping & food. Was there 2017 wouldn't let me put in that date.

I had a lovely time in Paris and a big reason was this hotel. It is in a great location, and the staff is absolutely outstanding. They arranged transport to the airport, recommended great restaurants, helped find a rental car at a great rate- they could not have been any nicer! The room was excellent- very clean and comfortable. Breakfast is available and was traditional. If I ever get to Paris again, I will stay at this wonderful hotel.

We had a Nice stay in this small hotel.
Nice and spaceous chamber. It is situated in a quite street nearby thé Arc the triomphe.
There was one bad thing, the Elevator was really noisy.
The breaktfast is okay.

Arrived at the address listed by the hotel, but it was the wrong location! Called the receptionist and she directed me to go around the corner and a block over, try doing that with 4 suitcases (not happy) booked this place months in advance only to be given the (spare room behind the counter) at least that’s what it looked like. Only room downstairs, next to the toilet and elevator. Room smelled of taco meat due to the restaurant nearby. The room was below ground level of a dead end street that the window faced, didn’t feel safe at all! Bars on the windows! Room had a cold old feeling. Lamp shade was missing from the lamp, shower curtain was dirty, just a disappointment. We stayed all of 10 min (time is took me to find another place) then we left. I would not recommend this place to anyone! This was my first time in Paris and this hotel is not what I was going to settle for. Best of luck!

I booked this hotel for 3 nights for my family a few months ago and they took one night off my card to secure the reservation. They charged my family for the full 3 nights and haven't given back the amount for the one night they took of my card. I have been contacting them for a month now and no response so far.

Great location just a few blocks from the Arc d’Triomphe, the Champs Illysee, plenty of restaurants, and tour bus stops. We didn’t have breakfast at the hotel (so I can’t comment on the food), but there was a great bagel shop nearby where we had a great breakfast. The room was clean and had air conditioning, but I was most impressed by the newly remodeled bathroom and plenty of hot water. The bedding was also excellent compared to other hotels in Paris where we’ve stayed. Will definitely stay there again!

Very good stay in the heart of paris minutes away from metro station. The only negative point is that the elevator is tiny...other than that it was super :) very clean room and helpful.staff. will be back!!

Clean and comfortable. Attentive staff who are always willing to help. Fairly basic continental breakfast ... great coffee. Rooms need dirty carpet removed and replaced with flooring and rooms could use some paint. Tiniest elevator ever barely fits two people. Our family of three took three trips to get to our room with luggage in the mini elevator. Great location near L’arc de Triomphe.

The position was good, we request to the reception to clean the room but they didn’t clean and also they don’t change the bad sheets. The breakfast was poor,and the first day the water was not there and no one was there to ask for the water.The igiene need to be the first things!!!!

1. Elevator fits 2 people max
2. Room carpets dirty and dark
3. Furniture Old and stained
4. Breakfast is ok but the food gets cold and not replenished
5. The access is ringing a bell
6. Excellent LOCATION
7. Small & tight rooms

Good location and value for money.
The hotel is 2 minutes walking from the Arc De Triomphe and Charles De Gaulle metro/train station which allows you you easy travel in the city.
The team there was OK but we didn't had any special requests.
The room was fine and was cleaned every day but the shower was with mold in some places.

Great location and great value compared to other rooms in same vicinity. I booked this to be in easy walking distance of the Arc de Triomphe and the Champs-Elysées and was not disappointed.

Hotel is not a premium room but you are not having to pay premium price so that should not be the expectation.

Great hotel , in central location, friendly staff who speak good English and have sense of humour ! They have the smallest lift in the world and they should make it a tourist attraction. The lift fit one person and a suitcase !

General evaluation avarege worste thing cleaness.
Moquette in the room not clean enough. Matrass with a plastic cover that make the sleeping very uncomfortable. General clean room not enough. Breakfast simple but not bad

The staff was really Nice and makes you feel very welcome.
The room was ready sonner which is a big positive point since we were very tired and the bed is incredible.
The breakfast could be better, but its what you can expect from a 3 star hotel. If you dont like coffe or milk you end up not having Many choices to go....
I recommend the hotel.

The hotel has excellent location. Close to the bus stop for Orly and CdG airports and close to the popular attractions. Very kind receptionist, room is larger than average, everyting looks clean. No complains.

Location
The hotel is located just 200 m Walk from the Arc De Triomphe and just 120 m walk from the Metro station. Overall the location is excellent and was the primary reason for us to book this hotel.

Property
It’s a very small hotel with a total of 16 rooms. A small reception. There are only 4 rooms per floor. The lift is extremely small and can only accommodate 2 people at the most. Worst part is the lift is only till 5th floor and we had rooms at 6th floor. One had to haul up your luggage to 6th floor via stairs. My 70 year old mother was with me and had a difficult time climbing stairs from 5th floor to 6th floor. Everything about the hotel is cramped. Too little space.

Rooms
The rooms are small ( but I guess so are all other rooms in Paris) the rooms had the basic amenities and were ok. We had a family room on the top floor so we had a sun roof and a balcony. As I mentioned earlier rooms are small but they have all the basic facilities. Toilets and rooms are cleaned every day.

House Keeping
We didn’t really ask for anything. Anyways one had to carry your own luggage to room!!!! The cleaning was satisfactory though.

Restaurant
The basement of the hotel had a very small space which they called the restaurant!!. The breakfast was really basic. It didn’t even have a live eggs counter. Just the boiled eggs option and few breads and milk. I felt it was costly for 15 Euro per person. There are Mac Donalds and many cafes nearby so food can be avoided here.

Fitness center
Seriuosly…..LOL

Overall.
Superb Location and very friendly staff. Otherwise a very small place which gives a feeling of being claustrophobic.

Hotel room was clean and good sized, nice shower, lovely and quiet in the evening... a stones throw from its name sake and perfect for a solo or couple.

Just needs “do not disturb / please make up my room” sign ☺️

Considering my previous hotel in London was TINY and old... this felt like a treat! Patient and friendly staff who handled my very poor mumbled French in their stride... and didn’t blink an eye when I wandered in after midnight.

Would stay again.

Staff not friendly. room service don’t knock the door and go straight in the room no privacy one day I didn’t get my room cleaned when I asked the front desk the girl promised it’ll be cleaned but it wasn’t

Great location. Couple of minutes from Arc de Triomphe. Bars & restaurants near by so breakfast outside hotel is easy. Hotel small so nice & quiet. Bed & ensuite clean. Air conditioning. Safe easy to use. Good value.

We stayed here as a family of 4 (myself and my mum and 2 kids, 10 and 5). We stayed in the triple room for just one night and it was perfectly big enough for us. My mum slept on the small bed and was fine! Me and 2 kids in very large double bed.

Room was clean and comfortable and had everything we needed. We had breakfast the next morning which was lovely, buffet style hot and cold choices and something for adults and kids.

Location was great, very near arc de Triomphe but on a quieter side street. We could walk within 20/25 mins to Eiffel Tower even with a 5 year old!

In particular the staff were so friendly and helpful, couldn’t do enough to make our stay perfect. Thank you for having us, we would definitely visit again

Worst hotel ever. We stayed from 20th to 22nd Aug in 2 family rooms on 6th floor. We booked this hotel reading reviews and close proximity to arc de triomphe. The room keys didn’t work and had to get it sorted around 4 times. Worst reception guys who didn’t know what they were doing. Do not book if you have children. No lift to 6th floor and hazardous staircase if u have children n are on 6th floor. This is my 4th visit to Paris and worst hotel experience ever...

I stayed for 5 nights with my wife and two kids (6 and 3 yrs old) and we were given a room with a double bed and a smaller than single bed which was barely OK for my 6 yr old. The rooms are far too small.. Also in the room was a crib for my 3 yr old which again would just about fit him and he could only sleep in it for first few hours as it wasnt comfy at all. The hotel does not have a lobby; only a very small area by the reception. We did not take breakfast as I felt it to be too expensive for 13/7 Euros for adult/kids (come on atleast kids should be given free breakfast), also they dont prepare the breakfast themselves, they just order it from a bakery. Once a member of the staff apparently tried to boil the milk downstairs which set the fire alarm at 7 am in the morning and all the guests had to jump out of the rooms only to be told that it was a false alarm. The Wifi in the room is poor. There is a lift which can only take two people (or 1 person with luggage) so if you are a family chances are you would have to take the stairs or spend some time waiting for your turn. Overall not good value for the price paid

1. Location is very good just within walking distance from Arc de Triomphe also near to the metro station and touristic bus stop.
2. Staff are very cooperative.
3. Tea kettle availability.
4. The best thing for me was the availability of Towel dryers.
5.Good Wifi.

Negative points:
1. Rooms ar not soundproof but each floor containing only 2 rooms so the noise depends on your neighbors.
2. The pillow was not clean.
3. Very small sink.
4. Very small Lobby ,very small lift that hardly carries 2 persons.
5. The shower was so bad and when I asked to fix the problem they were not able to fix it in the same day, after 2 days they changed it when it was my last day of staying.
6. It is stated in the booking.com that the rooms are containing ironing facilities but we did not find it and when we asked for , it was not available for that day, second day they provided us.
7. A little overpriced.

Hotel was very nice and clean - staff was extremely helpful and responsive - location is close to the Arc but a little difficult to find. We only stayed one night but it was a good choice for us. Breakfast was typical European and fine for everyone.

Couldn't ask for a better location. Close to everything but located in a quieter street off the main road. Staff are always helpful and there to greet you with a smile. The room is generously sized and the windows can be opened which allows natural ventilation. The hotel is very tranquil which makes for a good night's sleep after a busy day of sightseeing. Couldn't think of any other better place to stay at. It complimented my stay in Paris

Excellent location , near the Metro station, market within 50 meters .
Comfortable bed. Nice receptionist (specially the girl) she helped us a lot.
Very small elevator. Very small bathroom.
Overalls good stay and recommend for others.

Very good and friendly staff, clean rooms and nicely decorated. Very good location 5 mins walk from Arc de Triomphe. Some details in terms of design bothers be such as the small sink in the bathroom. Overall very good hotel with good staff that were really helpful to everything we asked for.

Good option , excellent location close to key Paris attractions and bars and restaurants. Not luxurious , but reasonable cost / benefit relationship. Staff is very nice. Rooms are clean. Stayed there twice and would recommend

The hotel was very nice, clean, bright, and lovely. It also felt very secure. I came home late and the reception confirmed I was staying at the hotel. I would have loved to stay longer as it is a good price to room ratio, Small room/bed, but perfect for one person

Chose a hotel which is conveniently located to different tourist attractions. It also near the metro stations and bus stops. The hotel staff especially Nadege and Noureddine are very courteous and helpful. Excited to be back here again.

Nous avons été très satisfaites de l’accueil et du service á votre hôtel . Notre chambre était très propre et le personnel était á l’écoute de nos besoins. Nous recommendons, sans hesitation, l’hôtel Arc de Triomphe á toute personne désirant un endroit á Paris qui est chaleureux et très bien situé.

We have been more than satisfied of the welcome and services we received at the hotel l’Arc de Triomphe. The staff were very helpful and always there to meet our needs and helped us with our different queries. We recommend, without hesitation, the hotel Arc de Triomphe to anybody desiring a place in Paris that is very welcoming and very well situated.

It is a great hotel in the very center of Paris. The rooms very big enough and renovated. The hotel is close to Arc De Triomphe and the metro and RER station. We went to Disneyland for around 45 minutes. I would definitely recommend this hotel.

Stayed for 2 nights when my husband ran the Paris marathon. This hotel was perfect as it was close to the start and finish line. It is small but adequate. Very clean and very comfortable. The receptionist was extremely friendly, smiley and helpful. I would recommend this hotel to anyone planning on running the Paris marathon. My only complaint and reason for not rating 5 stars was both mornings we were woken very early by the cleaner as our room appeared to be next to the cleaning cupboard, there was not a lot of room for the cleaner but it seemed as though they did not consider the sleeping guests at all! Otherwise this is a great base for a short stay in Paris.

Located very close to the Arc of Triomf in a fantastic neighborhood with a lot of eating options in less than 10 min walk, my room was super spacious with a very comfortable bed and pillows and the bathroom recently renovated and very clean, breakfast is served in the basement and it is quite simple. The first girl at the reception was very friendly, the next 2 guys much less friendly, just in Paris a hotel like this, can be considered 3 stars, but in general lines to sleep and rest is very good

Great hotel, friendly and helpful staff. The room had everything we needed for our stay and we would not hesitate to book again. A short walk to the metro and some lovely restaurants in walking distance

Wow. The hotel room is much bigger than expected for Paris, and we were surprised by the promo Int’l of the metro and the arc de triumph. The staff were friendly, helpful and professional. We will be back!

Close to Arc de Triumphe (obviously..) nice basic hotel. Rooms quite oldish interior, but everything was very tidy and clean. Surroundings offer restaurants, supermarket, and all the basic things. Offers also breakfast (didn't try) and small mini bar in the room. Quiet street, but you can hear noises through the door - and the airconditioning was bit noisy, but I turned it off for the night - no really need for it during January. Some problems with the keycard, had to ask reception to re-code it three times during couple of days (and the keycard was not kept close to the mobile phone)

The Hotel was in such a perfect location, right near Arc De Triomphe. The staff were super friendly and helpful. The only downsides were the noise, the elevator is so loud it might as well of been in my room and you can here everyone talking in from floors below and above. But for the price and the location I did not mind so much.

Small but very comfortable hotel. Cosy room. Pretty close to Metro Station and very convenient to see all the monuments the city. many restaurants, supermarket and really close to Champs Elyses avenue.

Room Cleanliness was very bad! When we arived was no toilet paper and next day also, under the the bed alot of garbage, carpet unclean and with stains. Very frendly and helpfull receptionsts. Location and Breckfast was good,

Very good, but cleaning qaulity in bathroom is not good. Lot of hair on shower and floor!!! Bath towel quality might be better! Other things was ok! Breakfast was good, my kid say that for here is good!

We had a weekend to Paris booked as we were doing the Bateaux dinner cruise.our room was on the first floor facing the road. No issues. Room was clean and tidy. Bathroom was a good size and bed was comfortable. I thought €14 each for breakfast was a rip off especially as the cooked items were not replaced from 10am in the morning we were there. I asked for bread so I could gave toast but it was all limited and a bit of a rip off really. But other than that staff were helpful it was fine and walking distance to station and arc de triomphe(about 10minutes stroll)

The only good thing about this hotel is its location. The room was reasonable and ours was quiet however the service is absolutely terrible. My husband & I had no hot showers for three days. The male staff member at the front desk Abdel, was rude and dismissive from the start repeatedly stating there was nothing wrong with the water. When he eventually came to our room he said to get out of the shower and turn on the sink tap which would fix it. When we finally demanded he call the manager a technician was called and the water was fixed. We were given a couple of free breakfasts by the manager to "make up for the misunderstanding". We were glad we did not pay for the breakfast as was very lacking in everything including bowls, cutlery etc. Problems occur from time to time with hotel rooms however in the past we have always had them dealt with politely and quickly. The management of this hotel should choose their staff more carefully. We will never recommend this hotel to anyone.

Rooms were very small and the lift too even their triple room. Location is just ok . Expensive for the facilities. However, the staffing is very good and responsive. They will help you with everything.

break fast is soo bad and small place no mora table to eat when i come to eat my break fast Iam not finding table only 4 table and all food finshed just i fiound cerial becouse the amount of food is so less

Good stay in this hotel nadege was so kind and helpful I like sleeping in this hotel beds are good quality and my friends and i really enjoyed paris is a beautiful city and the hotel is close to the champs elysees

Room 1 is on the ground floor off reception- apparently used when hotel is at capacity.
I found it to be musty and smelling of smoke; fridge had half full wine bottle and used water bottle in it; carpet s quite stained; and there was an intermittent noise from the cupboard just outside the door that went on for most of the night and significantly disturbed my sleep.
Friends said their rooms on other levels were ok but if using this hotel stipulate you do not want the ground floor room. I got the impression from staff that it doubles as a staff room.

This is an absolutely fantastic location, very quiet within minutes of the metro and you can walk to the Eiffel Tower in 15 mins. We stayed in room 10, it has free wifi, air conditioning, noon checkout and the staff are very helpful. We will definitely be coming back .

Amazing location, lovely hotel, absolutely friendly and helpful staff. A short walk to the metro, easy to get around. Breakfeast was great. The room was big and spacy, and clean. We absolutely enjoyed our stay here :)

The room was a comfortable size and the mattress was not soft or hard,just right for me.The bathroom was adequate.The curtains kept out the light, It was nice to have restauaunts, food outlets and the Metro close at hand

The lift broke down while we were there and we were on the fourth floor! It was highly inconvenient having to climb four flights of stairs each time, and it was very difficult to bring suitcases down four flights at the end of our stay!

I'll be back again to the same place, I enjoyed to be near to the town and smart smiley staff, I'll recommend the hotel to my friends as I already know the hotel by one of my friends ...,
the trip was very good and my stay was great

I would certainly stay at this hotel again. It was close to one of the places on our list. The clerk was very welcoming and we could not stop saying how nice she was. The rooms were on the smaller side but comfy, and what we needed for our stay.

Considering the hotel is in Paris, it was shocking at how spacious the room was. And comfortable of course. Breakfast was not as variety as I expected but better than nothing. My room was facing the road, so at night, you can hear voices of people hanging around the street. Bed and towel were nice.

Staff were friendly, helpful, and spoke English (2/5 of our group only spoke Chinese). The hotel has a small lift which is very much appreciated when you have large suitcases. Our room was clean, spacious, and comfortable. The price is reasonable and pretty good value considering the amenities near by. The hotel is down a side road so it was a quiet night's sleep, it is probably worth noting that we're a group of heavy sleepers...
I would stay here again for my next trip to Paris.

I stayed at this hotel for my business around a week. I know hotels in Paris was quite expensive so I was not expecting much for this hotel given the price is reasonable (for Paris standard) and its good location (close to the Arc).

When I arrived at the hotel, I was pleasantly surprised that this little hotel had pretty much I wanted for my trip. It was actually very good deal for the price, I guess!

First, it's location. It is a minute away from the Arc and Champ Elysee, and also few minutes walk to Metro stations (Etoile station, Ternes station, and Argentine station). There are many shops, restaurants, cafes, bars, and supermarkets both on Mac-Mahon and Ternes Avenues. Pharmacies are also nearby. It was quite convenient for commuting as well as eating and drinking around the hotel as well.

Second, facilities and rooms. It is quite small hotel, so facility-wise you can't expect much, but it's very clean and everything is functioning. It has an elevator also (trust me, some cheaper range hotels do not have it!). The room is quite spacious with a bed, small working desk, closet and bathroom/shower room. A/C works quite well and the room was also clean (again, trust me, rooms in some cheaper range hotels sometimes smell bad and A/C or the heater does not work well!). Basically, all are just sufficient and functional. Great.

Third, service. I was not expecting much in terms of service in Paris, but again to my surprise, the receptionists were quite friendly, nice, warm, and helpful. Good English as well (sorry I didn't mean the French does not speak English, but I was actually expecting less). I think all of them were great, and I enjoyed meeting them at the reception everyday!

So all in all, I can expect nothing more at this hotel. It's just sufficient and efficient. Highly recommended if you are looking for a highly functional, reasonably priced, and conveniently located hotel. This hotel is the one!

This hotel was very central to the train line and an easy walk with suitcase. The staff were very friendly and most helpful on how to get to attractions. Some nice restaurants close by. Room was very clean. Would stay here again and recommend to others

Excellent breakfast. Clean room. Helpful and friendly staff at reception. Excellent location. Great value and affordable rooms. My stay was better here than at the Hyatt regency the night before. Would recommend for families.

Location of the hotel is very close to Arc de Triomphe and many other famous attractions. Very convenient to subways and airport transfers . The room was good and spacious. But the breakfast needs to improve big time even eggs are not available. Only croissants and coffee with some cold cuts !!!!!
Hope that because of the size of the hotel !!!!

Stayed at the hotel twice and always really pleased with the accommodation.
Very close to main attractions and great places to eat and drink.
Rooms are very spacious (which is unique for Paris) given the price.
Friendly staff and small average breakfast but enough to to set you up for the day.

Strongly recommend for business trips or couples get away!

very nice hotel i stayed in tripple room room with one kid was quite big than expected the only thing i didn't liked is the breakfast that was good too but very few variety overall everything was good and also very near to arc de triomphe just 4 mins walking distance and all the restaurants near by.

we stayed for a total of 2 nights. As we wanted to just have a short relaxing break. Hotel reception was polite, helpful and informative. Room was spacious and one of the most comfortable beds ive ever come across!! Better than mine at home! A couple of English channels on the TV would have been nice. Be warned lift very small! Breakfast selection rather limited, as only there for 2 morning it was fine however if there for a week or longer i feel i would have become quickly bored of the food. Location was perfect, one small road away from the arc de triomphe, shops and restaurants. We had an amazing time and would stay here again if going for a short break.

we stayed for 3 nights in room 3 on the 1st floor,
big room, (especially for central paris), think it is normally a family room.
very quite, we were at the back of the hotel, bit dark but lighting in room was good.
a very large, firm ,comfy bed. free wifi, and lift was romantic.
It is about 3 minute walk to arc de triomphe, and metro.
which is why I have given it an extra point.

Ok what a lovely small and tiny Hotel, for people who are not used to go to Europe you will face many issues with such hotel, starting with not bellboy or tiny elevators and small rooms, However this is the case in most of the budget hotels or small European hotels.
I booked the triple room as it was a great choice among other Hotels especially that we are traveling with a child, the room size is almost 18 Meter comparing to other hotels, which have 10, or 12 Meter and most of them you will not be able to put extra bed.
The room from inside is good , Old carpet , small wardrobe contains safety box and small fridge , the bath room was fine but for sure small, the hot water is extremely excellent any time you can get it easily , a small heater to keep you warm in the room and there is Air Condition for the summer time.
There is no coffee machine, no complimentary tea or coffee or water. There is no electric kettle; However, if you need hot water you can get it from the restaurant at basement floor. For sure if they will put such items, the cost will be higher.
Housekeeping was average doing the basics and keeping the room good to be used daily.
Some more lighting is required in the rooms and to change the carpet.
The location of the hotel is prefect is very close to arc de triomphe 5 mintues walking and 2 minutes walking to one entrance of Charles De Gaulle Etoile Metro Station and RER A (this is one of the main station in Paris you can access Disney land from it and most of the Metro lines , this is main station for the Yellow Line which lead you to the LE defense and the huge shopping centre). There many shops near the hotel within walking distance, Grocery, dry clean, Bakery, cafes and restaurants, pharmacy all the services are near you.
We did not try the restaurant, but it was small but good to start your day.
If you a person who will spend all his day out of the hotel you can go with this hotel and you will feel that you got a good deal.
All of the front desk staff are extremely good and professional, helpful, have knowledge and willing to assist you with a smile.
Thanks and for sure will stay their again.
Notice: if you are looking for a luxury hotel with huge elevator and many restaurants don’t choose this hotel because you will blame yourself only not any other people, what is mentioned her in the reviews is true and actual so pick a hotel which you will think is suitable for you.

The location of the hotel was very good. We had a couple of nice walks that weekend. The receptionist was very friendly and gave us some good tips to eat out. For a 3-star hotel it was better than expected. Rooms were small but clean. The shower was good, bed was comfortable (for me but not for my wife). Breakfast was included in our reservation it was a bit limited but not too bad. A local bakery would give more option

Stayed at hotel for two nights. Travelling with family, we booked two rooms. One was supposed to be a double room and the other was triple occupancy.

First impressions seemed favourable. The lady at reception was pleasant and helpful upon us checking in. However bearing in mind there was 5 of us in total we were presented with just one key card per room.

Our rooms were on the 3rd floor (the only two rooms on that floor). The lift up to the floor was not really fit for purpose as even without luggage you could barely fit two people into it.

Once we finally managed to make our way upstairs with our bags the rooms were quite a shock, but not in a good way. Firstly the room that was supposed to be triple occupancy was considerably smaller than the room allocated for 2 people. The double bed was not a double (two singles pushed together). The sleeping provisions for the third person was frankly disgraceful. You could not even describe it as camp bed. I am not sure what you would call it.

The other room, as stated was much larger, and again with a large double bed that wasn't (two beds pushed together). The furnishings were tatty, the valance sheet on the bed was ripped an torn. The curtains looked tired and old and were not attached to rails properly.

The bathroom was logistically not well appointed. You needed to be some kind of contortionist to sit on the toilet. The shower controls were infuriating to say the least and the water temperature wildly inconsistent. We were not provided with a shower mat until the second day.

Other issues with the room. The air conditioning unit was placed directly above the TV, so from a health and Safety perspective a tad dangerous. It also made numerous noises even when off which did not lead to best of sleeps. That allied to fact that you could hear the goings on in the bathroom upstairs from us as well.

The room, had a safe, standard procedure. yet there was instructions only in French. Hardly helpful to travellers of other nations.

The hotel also offered free wi-fi, yet instead of being advised of this on check in and given the password, you had to contact reception to ask them.

Also, due to the small lift space, the best bet was to take the stairs, which were not best lit.

Also on morning of our check out (which was midday). We left the hotel at 10.00am to get something to eat, only to return to find neither card key working. No explanation or apology was offered by reception staff.

Finally on check-out we asked if we could leave our luggage at the hotel as we were not travelling back until early evening. Fine they said, Do you have a secure room we said. No, we just leave them in reception. Hmmmm

All in all a disappointing stay. The numerous small faults and irritants just added up over the course of our stay. This is one hotel too which I would not return, as even though cheap by comparison to many others in the area it still did not represent value for money.

Yes, that's an intentional pun in the title of this review — the fact that l'Hotel Arc de Triomphe is a mere two blocks from l'Etoile (which means "star" in French, for anyone who doesn't speak French) is one of its chief virtues. It's super-convenient to one of the drop-off points for the Air France buses from CDG (les cars Air France), as well as to a Europcar car rental office. It's a pleasant neighborhood to walk around in. There are many nearby patisseries, restaurants, and other amenities. And there are several Metro lines that converge at the Etoile stop.

But that's not all. The rooms are decent-sized for Paris, nicely decorated, and spick-and-span clean. The towels and linens are top-quality. And the breakfast is as good as any we've had in a Paris hotel (though, admittedly, we've never stayed at the George V).

And on top of all that, all the staff we encountered were friendly and helpful.

We noted a few equivocal and even some unfavorable comments — amidst much praise — in some other reviews and, now having stayed there, we can only assume those came from people not familiar with Parisian and/or French hotels. We have stayed at four different hotels in Paris (and at probably 25 or 30 all around France) and are henceforth devoted fans of l'Hotel Arc de Triomphe!

I stayed their with my family last October in a five says visit to beautiful Paris, a very nice hotel with perfect location, maybe a little bit small for those who never visited Paris before, but trust me their rooms are considered large compared to other hotels :)
Highly recommended if you prefer something walking distance to Champs Eleysees.

Fantastic location. Very friendly and helpful staff. Bathroom was small with only a shower but it worked and was clean. I shared a room with our 2 daughters and my husband shared a room with our two sons. Breakfast was good. Lots of restaurants locally for supper. My only complaint would be that the bed was VERY hard!!

I stayed there for 5 days woth my family, a very nice hotel, perfect location and friendly staff. Totally recommended if you want something just few walks from downtown and access to whole Paris through metro etoile.

I liked this hotel. You would have thought that with its name and address that it would be on one of the main branches from the Arc de Triomphe itself, but its actually a road from one of the main branches which can be confusing if you are coming back to the hotel late after a night of revelry in Paris. What seemed so easy in the light of day becomes much more challenging when it gets dark!

That said, the location is still great and the room they provided for us was excellent. More than enough space for 2 although the toilet was a bit small. The service was also good with English speaking front desk operator. The downside for this hotel is the absolutely tiny lift. It can at most fit 2 persons or 1 person + luggage. Wife and I had to make 2 trips to bring our luggage up on check in and bring it down on check out as we were on the 4th floor.

Another thing which may be annoying is that the door is kept locked when the only front desk operator is not around or at night. Also, when air conditioning is turned on, the console is a large blue light which is very annoying when you are trying to sleep.

We didn't try the food here so can't really comment on that. I do think however that it is very good value for money.
